{
  "title": "GatewayZ — Cache & Redis CPU Profile",
  "uid": "gatewayz-cache-layer-profile",
  "description": "Pyroscope CPU breakdown of every Redis/cache operation in the gateway. Each operation is tagged with cache_layer (auth, rate_limit, model_catalog, response_cache, trial_analytics) and cache_op (read, write, delete) — making it possible to answer: 'Is Redis actually hurting us, and which layer is to blame?'",
  "tags": ["profiling", "pyroscope", "redis", "cache", "performance"],
  "schemaVersion": 39,
  "version": 1,
  "refresh": "30s",
  "time": { "from": "now-1h", "to": "now" },
  "timepicker": {},
  "panels": [
    {
      "id": 9000,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "",
      "transparent": true,
      "pluginVersion": "11.5.2",
      "gridPos": { "x": 0, "y": 0, "w": 24, "h": 6 },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "## GatewayZ — Cache Layer Profile\n\nRedis-backed LLM response cache analytics: hit rates, miss penalties, eviction patterns, and cost savings from cache hits.\n\n| Signal | Target | Notes |\n|--------|--------|-------|\n| ✅ **Cache Hit Rate** | > 60% | < 40% = cache key schema or TTL issue |\n| ⏱️ **Cache Miss Latency** | = full LLM call latency | Baseline for cache value measurement |\n| 💰 **Cost Savings** | Hits × avg token cost | Track cumulative savings from caching |\n| 🔄 **Eviction Rate** | Low | High eviction = cache is too small or TTL too short |\n\n_Profiles from Pyroscope · Navigate: [Infrastructure & Caching](#) for Redis ops health · [Model Usage](#) for token cost analytics_"
      },
      "fieldConfig": { "defaults": {}, "overrides": [] }
    },
    {
      "id": 1,
      "type": "row",
      "title": "🔍 Cache CPU Flamegraph — What is Redis actually doing?",
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": { "x": 0, "y": 6, "w": 24, "h": 1 }
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "",
      "gridPos": { "x": 0, "y": 7, "w": 24, "h": 2 },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "**How to read this dashboard:** Each flamegraph sample was captured while the process was inside a `pyroscope.tag_wrapper(cache_layer=..., cache_op=...)` block — meaning only stack frames executing a Redis operation are shown. A tall, wide block means that cache layer consumed significant CPU. Filter by layer or operation using the variables above to isolate exactly which call is costly."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "type": "flamegraph",
      "title": "Cache Operation CPU Flamegraph",
      "description": "CPU stack samples taken while inside a Redis/cache operation. Filter by cache_layer (auth, rate_limit, model_catalog, response_cache, trial_analytics) and cache_op (read, write, delete) to zoom in on the expensive path.",
      "datasource": { "uid": "grafana_pyroscope", "type": "grafana-pyroscope-datasource" },
      "gridPos": { "x": 0, "y": 9, "w": 24, "h": 16 },
